Anything that is surrounded by quotation marks is called a string. This is how a computer represents words or sentences. For example, &ldquo;a&rdquo;, &ldquo;2&rdquo;, &ldquo;banana!&quot;, and &ldquo;Hello World&rdquo; are strings, but 2 and Hello World are not strings, because the quotation marks are missing. You can combine many strings together using the + sign!
For example,
&quot;Apple&quot; + &quot;Pineapple&quot; produces the string &quot;ApplePineapple&quot;
&quot;Nuevo&quot; + &quot; &quot; + &quot;Foundation&quot; produces &quot;Nuevo Foundation&quot;

